The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board has released timetable for this year’s Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination and Direct Entry examination. According to the board, the UTME would hold from Saturday, Saturday 5, to June 19, 2021. The board said registration for the examinations will start on Thursday, April 8 to Saturday, May 15, 2021, it said. The board said there will be no extension of time for the sale of the UTME/DE application documents. The board made the announcement in a statement by its Head, Public Affairs and Protocol, Dr. Fabian Benjamin on Wednesday. According to the statement, the Governing Board of JAMB took the decision after its meeting on March 22, 2021. The statement said applicants will have to supply  their National Identity Number (NIN) before they can register for the examinations.